DataElement.preferredName: Obesity Three Factor Eating Questionnaire Assessment Score
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Having a high amount of body fat (body mass index [BMI] of 30 or more)._A natural number greater than 2 and less than 4 and the quantity that it denotes: the sum of two and one._Anything that contributes causally to a result._To take food into the body by mouth._Predetermined sets of questions used to collect data - clinical data, social status, occupational group, etc. The term is often applied to a self-completed survey instrument._The final result of a determination of the value, significance, or extent of._A number or range of numeric values measuring performance, function, quality, or ability.
